# Si-Chip Cursor Bridge

This bridge tells Cursor that whenever the user is working on Si-Chip BasicAbility profiles,
dogfood rounds, half-retire decisions, or router-tests, the authoritative Skill body lives at
`.cursor/skills/si-chip/SKILL.md` (mirrored from `.agents/skills/si-chip/SKILL.md`) and the
governing rule layer is `AGENTS.md` (compiled from `.rules/si-chip-spec.mdc`).

## When to Apply

- Authoring or editing `.local/dogfood/<DATE>/round_<N>/{basic_ability_profile,metrics_report,...}.yaml`
- Producing `half_retire_decision.yaml` (must have numeric 7-axis value_vector per spec §6)
- Running router-test sweeps against `templates/router_test_matrix.template.yaml`
- Diagnosing R6 metric coverage against `templates/basic_ability_profile.schema.yaml`

## Hard Rules (inherited from AGENTS.md / spec §11.1 — NEVER violate)

- No marketplace.
- No router model training.
- No Markdown-to-CLI converter.
- No generic IDE compatibility layer.

## Source-of-truth invariant

Edits to the Skill body MUST be applied to `.agents/skills/si-chip/SKILL.md` (the canonical source);
`.cursor/skills/si-chip/SKILL.md` is a generated mirror — drift between the two is a CI failure
(see `.local/dogfood/<DATE>/round_<N>/raw/cursor_sync_drift.json`).
